`cde.desktop`:
Adds the CDE session entry to display managers (`/usr/share/xsessions`).

`cde-session`:
Session launcher that starts optional desktop services (`picom`, `dunst`) and runs Qtile in X11 mode with `/etc/cde/default_config.py`.

`default_config.py`:
System-wide CDE Qtile config. Floating-only workflow with taskbar and launcher keybinds.

`cde-settings`:
Small GUI app to update CDE user settings at `~/.config/cde/settings.json`.

`cde-settings.desktop`:
Desktop launcher entry for the CDE Settings app.

`99-qtile.rules`:
udev rules used by Qtile-supported hardware integrations.
